items.name: Self foot licking (anime)
items.description:
Well... the name speaks for itself.

Please use the following prompt to activate properly this lora :

1girl, close up, tongue out, saliva, soles, YOUR DETAILS, <lora>

Example : 1girl, close up, tongue out, saliva, soles, nurse, red eyes, hospital, <lora:selfFootLickingAnime_v10:0.6>

Tested on Anything v4.5 and Anyhentai, but it should work on most anime models. I suggest between 0.6 and 0.8 for the lora weight.

Since it was trained at 768x768 resolution, it seems to work much better if you generate at 768x768 (or 640x640 if you can't generate at higher resolution).

The pose is very specific so there isn't much room for variety.

Sample images setting :

  • Euler a

  • 24 steps

  • 768x768

  • Anyhentai model

  • Hires :

    • realESRGAN_4xplus_anime_6B

    • upscale by 1,5

    • denoising strength: 0,2

It's a work on progress so it can produce some weird results, but don't hesitate to share your images !

items.name: „ÄêArt Style„ÄëSadakage Style
items.description:
2023/6/26 update

Update dataset. Retrain the model using new craft.

Introduction

A LoRA model trained with ~110 images by Sadakage. The trigger tag is ‚Äòsadakage‚Äô. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

  • Some preview images are generated using hires fix. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Emily Ratajkowski
items.description:
Emily O'Hara Ratajkowski (born June 7, 1991) is an American model, actress, and author. Born in London to American parents and raised in Encinitas, California, her modeling debut was on the cover of the March 2012 issue of the erotic magazine treats! which led to her appearing in Maroon 5's music video "Love Somebody".

If you like my work, a review is more than welcome! Also, follow me on Twitter or Instagram!

Looking for something... spicy? Here's my Patreon!

This is a textual inversion of the amazing Emily Ratajkowski. I used 40 public images of her, with a 5300 steps training process. Hope you'll like it! To use it in your works:

  • download the file and place it into stable-diffusion-webui>embeddings folder;

  • add emrata91 to your prompt;

  • keep the sampling steps around 30, CFG between 7 and 8 seems to work well. Very good results with DPM++ SDE Karras & Realistic Vision. Check the gallery for some inspiration!

items.name: Natsume [My Senpai is Annoying / Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi]
items.description:
The cheeky Natsumi from the anime series

How to use
Start with "ntsmstyle", "1girl" and then with whatever you want. Depending on what you prompt/model/other LoRAS you can also add "short hair" and "yellow eyes" to strengthen the appearance further.

Misc
512 resolution trained on NAI without noise offset option for best LoRA compatibility. Dataset based on 39 screencaps from the anime series.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

All images are raw untouched txt2img, no inpainting or post-processing done.

items.name: Eris
items.description:
Eris, the Greek goddess of strife and discord.

This is my first pure 3D render/Cartoon model. When I started working on this model I had almost zero knowledge on writing prompts for 3d renders/CGI. As such, my main goal for this model was quickly realized - Make a model that accepts photorealistic prompts and returns beautiful 3D rendered outputs. Normal 3D render/CGI prompts also work with this model.

Important Settings

The following settings assume you're using webui by Automatic1111

  • USE CFG VALUES BELLOW 8*

    • This model does not respond well to CFG values above 8. With some caveats that will be explained bellow.

    • Do not go over 6 CFG with Euler a unless,

    • You are using Hires Fix. I found that you can go as high as 10 CFG with hires. fix enabled. This applies to all samplers.

    • DPM++ SDE Karras starts to degrade around 7 CFG if using clip skip = 1, no hires fix. However, if you're using DPM++ SDE Karras with clip skip = 2 the CFG values can go up to at least 10 CFG without significant (if any) degradation.

    • General Advice:

      • Do Not exceed 6 CFG with Euler a, unless using hires fix.

      • Do Not exceed 7 CFG with DPM++ SDE Karras with clip skip set to 1, unless using hires fix.

      • You Can go up to at least 10 CFG with DPM++ SDE Karras with clip skip set to 2, without using hires fix.

      • I could not test all samplers. If you notice broken compositions or distortions; lower your CFG value and/or enable hires fix. My own personal settings for hires fix can be found bellow.

    • Thanks to Duo V2 on the Unstable Diffusion discord for helping me get to the bottom of this issue.

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.safetensors

    • link - https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/sd-vae-ft-mse-original/blob/main/vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.safetensors

    • This is already baked into the model but it never hurts to have VAE installed.

    • Under Settings -> Stable Diffusion -> SD VAE -> select the VAE you installed via dropdown. Then, uncheck Ignore selected VAE for stable diffusion checkpoints that have their own .vae.pit next to them

  • Clip skip : 2

    • This varies. Most of the time Clip skip = 2 works best with this model. In the event you're not getting the results you want. First, try Clip skip = 1.

  • ETA Noise Seed Delta: 31337

    • Found in - Settings -> Sampler parameters -> Eta noise seed delta

  • Sigma Noise: 1

  • Sigma Churn: 0 or 1

    • Optional - When using Euler, Heun, DPM2 samplers try setting Sigma Churn = 1

    • Found in - Settings -> Sampler parameters -> sigma churn

  • Optional Negative Textual Inversion (TI): bad_prompt_version2

    • link - https://huggingface.co/datasets/Nerfgun3/bad_prompt/blob/main/bad_prompt_version2.pt

    • Install to - stable-diffusion-webui -> embeddings

    • In webui - Add (bad_prompt_version2:0.8) at the end of your negative prompt.

  • Optional Recommended Samplers:

    • DPM++ SDE Karras // 18-35 steps

    • Euler // 40 - 80 steps // Sigma Churn : 1

    • DPM++ 2M Karras // 40 - 70 steps

    • DPM++ 2S a Karras // 30 - 75 steps

    • Heun // 20 - 30 steps // Sigma Churn : 1

    • DPM2 // 30 - 75 steps // Sigma Churn : 1

    • These are just recommendations; feel free to experiment with different values and samplers.

  • Optional Hires. Fix settings (these are my go-to parameters):

    • Upscaler : R-ESRGAN 4x+

    • Denoising strength: 0.3 - 0.35

    • The rest of the settings are up to you. They don't really impact the quality of the output.

    • Note: Hires Steps, if you're using high steps for SD - You can choose a hires step value lower than your SD step value. This will increase the generation times.

      • For example; Let's say you're using Euler sampler @ 60 steps. You can then set the Hires Steps to ~40. Apposed to the default which is 0. Hires Steps = 0 means it will follow the same step value as sampler (Euler in this case). Lower Hires Step values will reduce generation time.

  • Optional Face Restoration:

    • I use CODEFORMER @ 0.8 strength. Whether or not you use face restoration is up to you.

  • Optional Quick Settings:

    • For easier access to some of the settings in webui, you can move some settings sliders/dropdowns to the main interface (beside model selection).

    • Quick settings location -

      • Settings -> User interface -> Quicksettings list

    • My Quick settings -

      • sd_model_checkpoint, CLIP_stop_at_last_layers, s_churn

      • Where:

        • CLIP_stop_at_last_layers is Clip Skip

        • s_churn is sigma churn

PDF documentation is in the works.

items.name: Double Exposure (Photo Edition) for 2.x
items.description:
MAKE SURE TO READ THE INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY

This is the Double Exposure model for SD 2.x specialized in clean, photorealistic content. To get the very best results it's highly recommended to follow some rules concerning composition and especially prompting:

  • The model was trained on subjects of women and men combined with nature (forests, trees, leaves, mountains) and cities (buildings and roads). Different animals can be triggered but might take more effort to get good results.

  • To achieve the very best results the prompt should be composed in this style:

That is: token + composition + subject made out of + nature/architecture, background color.

The phrase made out of is central. Look more into successful prompting through the example images posted on this page.

If you want an even simpler prompt composition this sort of setup will work, but the results might be less accurate:

dblxp double exposure close-up profile woman forest, background color

Installation

Pick either the .ckpt or .safetensor file version of the model and put it in the models directory of your Automatic1111 installation - models\Stable-diffusion. You trigger the model with the token dblxp.

Hope you get good results and I look forward to you sharing them with everyone!

items.name: Adolf Diffusion
items.description:
Adolf Diffusion

IMPORTANT NOTES:

>This model is NOT meant to share or glorify any political view.

>Trigger word: "AdolfHitler". Recommended weight: 0.7 and higher

>Trained on b&w pictures, in order to get good results appropriate prompting and model is required.

>The best results achieved with realistic models (Realistic Vision, Deliberate).

>Probably the easiest way is to just use inpaint.

Prompting

>To get images in color use these:

  • Positive: in color

  • Negative: monochrome, black and white, b&w, greyscale

>To get rid of blurry background:

  • Negative: simple background, blurry background

>Trained mostly on upper body pictures, might be hard to get full body.

>If you have problems with getting Adolf's mustache, try setting the LoRa weight higher (or first generate image with low weight and then inpaint face with high weight).

>Eyes might sometimes be a problem, try experimenting with these:

  • Positive: looking at viewer, detailed eyes etc.

How to make similar model

I know this model is far from being great, but if someone wants to know the workflow, here you go:

1. Find good image and crop it (in my case 44 images). 2. Upscale it x2~x4 (in my case mostly R-ESRGAN). 3. Remove noise using any graphic software. 4. Scale down 5. Train LoRa (using Google Colab).

Also:

>Some of example images were created using ControlNet and img2img

>If you want to use my model anywhere feel free to do so, but it would be nice to put me in credits.

>For any questions you can contact me rafikxd123#7133

items.name: ComfyUI "Quality of life Suit:V2" (auto Update,Chat GPT , DallE-2 ,Math, ... and more )
items.description:
If you like my work Kindly like,rate and comment XD


These nodes are for : ComfyUI

ComfyUI:

ComfyUI is an advanced node based UI utilizing Stable Diffusion. It allows you to create customized workflows such as image post-processing, or conversions.

Auto Update:

-when you run comfyUI, the suit will generate a config file

The file looks like this :
{

"autoUpdate": true,

"branch": "main",

"openAI_API_Key": "sk-#################################"

}

this file is used to control Auto update, and to manage any other settings the tool requires

File Description:
"autoUpdate": can be (true) or (false),
"branch": default is ("main")

other options for branch:

  • "v2.1.X": means it will only update bug fixes for v2 version.

  • "main" means it will always be on latest stable build, this may add new nodes suddenly (also usually it assume you update comfy)

  • "develop": it will contain latest stuff I'm working on now, but may contain bugs

"openAI_API_Key": if you want to use the ChatGPT or Dall-E2 features, you need to add your open-AI API key, you can get it from (Account API Keys - OpenAI API)

How to use

  • you must update comfyUI first before using this version

As this version relies heavily on the new feature of comfyUI : the ability to switch inputs to be widgets and widgets to be inputs

  • Download the zip file.

  • Extract to ..\ComfyUI\custom_nodes : like this image :

  • restart comfy if it was running (reload web, not enough)

  • you will find my nodes under new group O/‚Ä¶

  • You can check the workflow folder to find great examples of how to use the tool

Kindly be notified that you can load the images in the downloaded ZIP/workflows in comfyUI to load the workflow that was used to generate it

Current Nodes:

//7/4/2023 -----------------------------------------------------------------

  • selectLatentFromBatchNode
    if you generate multiple images, it allows you to pick which to use
    for example, if you generate 4 images, it allows you to select 1 of them to do further processing on it

    or you can use it to process them sequentially

  • NSP
    this node allow you to select random value from SoupPrompts file

  • equations
    - this node allow you to perform math equations on the input
    - there are two variants
    - 1 input (X)
    - 2 inputs (X,Y)
    (you can convert the x and y to inputs by right click on them, so you can use values from another node)

    if you like this node tell me i can enhance it so you can select inputs number

// 22/3/2023 -----------------------------------------------------------------

OpenAI Nodes

OpenAI ChatGPT and DALLE-2 API as nodes, so you can use them to enhance your workflow
ChatGPT-Advanced

  • Load_openAI
    to initialize openAI for next nodes

Advanced ChatGPT nodes

  • chat_message :
    create a message to send it to chatGPT

  • combine_chat_messages:
    used to group messages together before sending them to chatGPT

  • Chat_Completion:
    the magic node this node will send the messages to ChatGPT and receive response from it , the response will be the output string

  • debug_Completion:
    this to help you check the whole response

in this workflow, I used ChatGPT to create the prompt,

  1. at start, I send 2 messages to ChatGPT

  2. first message is to tell ChatGPT how to behave and what is the prompt format that I need from him

  3. in the second message I send what I want in this case young girl dancing (I added young, so her clothes become decent XD don't misunderstand me please )

  4. after that I feed the messages to the completion node ‚Äúit is called like that in their API sorry‚Äù

  5. and congrats, you have a nice input for your image

DallE-2 Image nodes

  • create_image:
    used to create and image using DALLE-2 for now only 1 image each time, will update it in next patch to allow multiple images

  • variation_image:
    this node will generate variations similar to the image you send to it

this is a full workflow where

1- use ChatGPT to generate a prompt

2- send that prompt to DALLE-2

3- give the generated image to Stable Diffusion to paint over it

4- use DALLE-2 to create variations from the output

ChatGPT-simple

This node harnesses the power of chatGPT, an advanced language model that can generate detailed image descriptions from a small input.

  • You need to have OpenAI API key , which you can find at https://beta.openai.com/docs/developer-apis/overview

  • Once you have your API key, add it to the api_key.txt file

I have made it a separate file, so that the API key doesn't get embedded in the generated images.

<you can load this image in comfyUI to load the workflow>

String Suit

add multiple nodes to support string manipulation also a tool to generate image from text

  • String:
    node that can hold string (text)

  • Debug String
    this node will write the string on the console

  • Concat string
    this node is used to combine two strings together

  • Trim string
    this is used to remove any extra spaces at the start or the end of a string

  • Replace string & replace string advanced
    used to replace part of the text by another part

  • >>>> String2image <<<<
    this node will generate an images based on a text, which can be used with controlNet to add text to the image.
    ‚Äî the tool support fonts ‚Äúadd the font you want in fonts folder‚Äù
    ‚ÄúIf you load the example image in comfyUI the workflow that generated it will be loaded‚Äù

  • >>>>CLIPStringEncode <<<
    The normal ClipTextEncode node but this one receive the text from the string node, so you don't have to retype your prompt twice anymore

in this example I used depth filter but if you are using WAS nodes you can convert the text to canny using WAS canny filter it will give much better results with the canny controlNet

Other tools

  • LatentUpscaleMultiply:
    it is a variant from the original LatentUpscale tool but instead of using width and height you use a multiply number
    for example, if the original images dimensions are (512,512) and the mul values were (2,2) the result image will be (1024,1024)
    also you can use it to downscale if needed by using fractions ex:(512,512) mul (.5,.5) ‚Üí (256,256)
    Node Path: O/Latent/LatentUpscaleMultiply


there are also many brilliant nodes in this package
WAS's Comprehensive Node Suite - ComfyUI | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

thanks for reading my message, I hope that my tools will help you.

modelVersions.name: v1.0  ChatGPT
modelVersions.description:
HINT!: you can load the wizard image to load the workflow and see examples of how the ChatGPT node can be used in a workflow.

Add following (node/nodes):

  • ChatGPT node
    This script is a custom node for ComfyUI that utilizes the OpenAI module to generate responses based on a given prompt.

Usage

To use this script in your ComfyUI project, follow these steps:

  1. Copy the ChatGPT_O.py file to your custom_nodes directory in your ComfyUI project.

  2. Create a file named api_key.txt in the custom_nodes directory and paste your OpenAI API key in it. Account API Keys - OpenAI API

  3. In your ComfyUI project, add a new custom node and select ChatGPT_O as the node class.

  4. Provide a prompt for the script to generate a response for.

Inputs

The node takes two inputs:

  1. prompt: a multiline string input for the prompt.

  2. api_key_file: a string input for the name of the file containing the OpenAI API key. By default, the script looks for a file named api_key.txt in the custom_nodes directory.

Output

The node returns a string containing the response generated by the GPT-3.5-turbo model.

Dependencies

This script requires the OpenAI module to be installed. If it is not already installed, the script will install it automatically.

Author

This script was developed by Omar and can be found on their Github page at https://github.com/omar92. Contact Omar on Discord at Omar92#3374.

PLEASE NOTE: The images you will receive when using this model unmixed will not in any way, shape, or form resemble the images provided here, which were generated by mixing this model with RealisticVision1.4. I trained this on 640 photographs of crime scenes from the 1910s, taken from the NYC municipal archives. My intention was to make a thing that would generate random crime scenes for a noir/detective project without any need for prompting, and in that, it succeeds, though as a stand-alone, it is very much a one-trick-pony. It is very, very, very strong and inflexible‚Äîprompting is nearly useless‚Äîbut I have mixed it with a few other ckpts to good effect (~30% of cr1m3 in the mix for best results, in my testing.) and you are encouraged to fuss around with it.

NOTE: If you see long crutch-looking metal poles around the edges of your synths, this is because many of the photos in the training data featured these. They're tripod legs.

items.name: Pinocchio 1.6
items.description:
If you like this then please buy me a coffee sometime: https://www.buymeacoffee.com/Darkseal

The images attached might look like a celebrity freak show for some but let me explain:

This is Pinocchio model with 1.5 face weights re-injected back into it using the merge block weights tool. Please see image below. By doing this we obtain the closest results to the famous actors and actresses 1.5 was trained on. In the celebrity images, I have not given much thought to the prompt, I have left face fix OFF, there is no hires up-scaling (except for the main image of Tom), there are NO embedding or loras. This will make using loras or embedding as close as possible at low power values while keeping the model as free as possible to prompt the environment. This way even the worst embedding\ti\lora trained on 1.5 should work as expected, let alone a good one.

Following the information found here: https://rentry.org/Merge_Block_Weight_-china-_v1_Beta#31

Please note... what we gain in faces we loose in penises. Yes, that's right. Gaining famous faces removed the heads of penises. When using penis prompt please use some kind of embedding or lora to correct the horror that is the penis heads in this model.

items.name: Casca (Berserk)
items.description:
Lora model for Casca from Berserk. This one is rather simple and was trained on small number of images. I mostly avoided using manga images because I was going for more generic style and didn't wanted to channel Miura style.

Most of previews were made with weight 0.9. I still think it's easier to use lower weight, but since this model was faster to train I played around and was hoping to make it work well at weight 1. In the end through it felt like I'm sacrificing accuracy for an easy to change number so I wasn't forcing it.

Armor outfit - casca \(berserk\), breastplate, brown gloves, thigh boots, shoulder armor, cape, pelvis curtain

Dress - casca \(berserk\), dress, choker, white gloves

Casual outfit - casca \(berserk\), capelet, shirt, pants

I was really only going for the armor outfit, but there have been some singular images in training set with other outfit and it looks like model learned them somewhat ok, maybe except for casual pants which feels mostly random ^_^;

You might want to put things like sheath, sword, holding weapon, unsheating in your negative prompts because this kind of pose was quite common in training set and you can often encounter this happening unprompted.

You can add dark skin or dark-skinned female if you're ending up with skin tone that feels too light for you.

items.name: Ilulu (Miss Kobayashi's Dragon Maid)
items.description:
Trigger word: ilulu \(maidragon\)

Recommended weight: 0.8-1.0

Useful descriptions: pointy ears, low twintails &| twintails, colored tips, red eyes | orange eyes, slit pupils, sharp teeth, yellow horns, dragon tail & dragon girl, shortstack | petite

Character can be generated without additional descriptions just fine, but in case you don't get what you want try using them in your prompt.

  • v2-Epoch11: should better draw her twintails and horns in cases where it doesn't. Updated Data Set: added some missing poses tags, "dragon girl" for pictures where there is "dragon tail", and removed Hair Length and Hair Color (with exception of "colored tips").

  • Epoch8: may better depict the character, but may start losing prompt details.

  • Epoch5: may follow original image better, but may not get some character features as good.

This lora was trained on 80 different pictures of the character with 3 repeats. I was trying to train it on many different models and in the end, between Anything-v3 and NAI, decided to land on Anything-v3 as it seemed to produce better results. Data with her dragon hands seems to have made Lora worse, so I decided to exclude them. All images shown were used with different models at either strength 0.8 or 1.0.

The models used for preview images are: MeinaMix v8, Grapefruit v4.0, Color Box Model, DualPersonality - Normal Line, Animelike 2.5D, GuaMix3;

items.name: Nakano Miku Character LoRA
items.description:
Nakano Miku Character LoRA

If you enjoy my models and want to support me you could buy me a coffee!

This LoRA mimics the character Nakano Miku from The Quintessential Quintuplets.

The example images were created with NeverEndingDream on varying weight (I recommend from 0.5-0.7 depending on the style you want) but feel free to experiment on your own. I tried briefly to mix it with a couple of different embeddings and it gave back decent results but you might find a better way to mix them (changing different weights etc.).

To change the weight just change the '1' in this prompt: <lora:nakano-Miku-LoRA:1>.

I'd love to see the art you guys make with it so feel free to add them in comments.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: The Grand Budapest Hotel
items.description:
I'm excited to introduce to you my textual inversion, which is based on the movie "The Grand Budapest Hotel" directed by Wes Anderson. Using this model, you can generate photos with a similar style to "The Grand Budapest Hotel".

Although "The Grand Budapest Hotel" used three different aspect ratios in the movie, we only used the 4:3 aspect ratio movie frames for training. Therefore, when generating images, it is best to manually adjust the frame size to 480x360. This will ensure the best results in generating images with a similar style to "The Grand Budapest Hotel".

The model is based on the SD1.5 standard model, which means it is suitable for the SD1.5 model. The model is trained on a large dataset, so it can produce suitable images.

However, since the images used are movie screenshots and have unnecessary black borders, the generated images may have black edges. We are working to address this issue and will improve it in future versions.

Overall, as a fan of Wes Anderson's unique style and "The Grand Budapest Hotel" in particular,I hope that this model will introduce more people to the world of Wes Anderson and the beautiful, distinctive aesthetic of "The Grand Budapest Hotel".

By the way, If you like my work, feel free to buy me a cup of coffee. Thank you very much for your support!

items.name: Deemo Artstyle LoRA
items.description:
LoRA trained on the artstyle of the game Deemo, as requested by Yui9987.

Specifically, it was trained on some of the song artworks.

Trigger word is deemoArtstyle.

Use "deemo" to generate the character, but getting it to generate deemo alongside another character can be difficult. It sometimes fuses them into one shadowy being.

I recommend weight around ~0.8-1.

It is a bit difficult to use as the original artworks are rather abstract, but it's fun to play around with.

Trained on AnythingV4.5.

items.name: Shadowverse / Granblue Fantasy Filene LoRA
items.description:
It's Filene, but now in LoRA form. A bit of an expanded dataset and better tagging than the TI embed from earlier. You can use both together if you like. I took particular care in trying to train on as many from behind and from side images as possible so that the tail looks good from any angle. You still get the occasional detached or misplaced tail when prompting not from front, but you should be able to roll into a good looking tail pretty easily.

As always, trained base NAI with FULL TAGS. That means that the costume was always prompted during training, so you MUST TAG IT AS IN THE EXAMPLE IMAGES.

A few training images were with her bodysuit costume, but not enough to get it really accurate. You can try it if you like though - see example.
